    %% ============================================================================
    %% NOTES
    %% ============================================================================
    %%
    %% IMPORTANT CONCEPTS:
    %%
    %% 1. Time Travel is NOT a backup:
    %%    - It's a recovery window, not a long-term backup
    %%    - Data still in Snowflake (subject to account deletion)
    %%    - For true backups, export data externally (S3/Azure/GCS)
    %%
    %% 2. Storage costs are SIGNIFICANT:
    %%    - 90-day retention = 3x storage cost (active + TT + FS)
    %%    - Example: 100 TB table = $3,000/month active + $3,000 TT + $300 FS = $6,300/month
    %%    - Balance compliance needs vs. cost
    %%
    %% 3. Time Travel queries have same performance as normal queries:
    %%    - Snowflake manages micro-partition versions transparently
    %%    - AT(TIMESTAMP) queries are NOT slower
    %%    - Can use all SQL features (joins, aggregations, etc.)
    %%
    %% 4. Fail-Safe vs. Backups:
    %%    - Fail-Safe: Snowflake's safety net (7 days, auto, disaster recovery)
    %%    - Backups: Your responsibility (exports, cross-region replication)
    %%    - Best practice: External backups for critical data
    %%
    %% 5. Transient vs. Permanent tables:
    %%    - Transient: No Fail-Safe, max 1-day Time Travel, lower cost
    %%    - Permanent: Full Time Travel + Fail-Safe, higher cost
    %%    - Use transient for staging/temp data
    %%
    %% RECOVERY TIME OBJECTIVES (RTO):
    %% - UNDROP TABLE: < 1 second
    %% - CLONE AT(TIMESTAMP): 1-10 seconds (instant metadata)
    %% - CREATE TABLE AS SELECT AT(): Minutes to hours (data copy)
    %% - Fail-Safe recovery: 12-48 hours (Support ticket)
    %%
    %% RECOVERY POINT OBJECTIVES (RPO):
    %% - Time Travel: Granularity down to the second
    %% - Fail-Safe: Determined by when data entered Fail-Safe
    %% - Transaction consistency: Always maintained
    %%
